label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 235: Kitāb al-Adwār
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Treatise on the theory of music, including division of frets, ratio of intervals, consonance and dissonance, cycles, rhythmic and melodic modes, and the 5-string oud or lute, with an anonymous commentary.
        Language: Arabic
        Support: paper
        Extent: 
        Collation: 
        Layout: Written in 28 long lines, with some diagrams arranged in 2 columns (for example, p. 9-12)
        Script: Written in a naskh script.
        Decoration: Diagrams and selected characters and words in red ink throughout.
        Binding: Rebound in contemporary leather over boards, blind-stamped and blind-tooled.
        Origin: Written in the Ottoman Empire in the 16th century.
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 235
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 5056923 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/5056923
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/LJSchoenbergManuscripts/html/ljs235.html
